-- Pound Stays Higher Versus Dollar, Euro After ECB Cuts Rate
-- B y   M a r k   M c C o r d
-- 2013-05-02T11:51:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/pound-stays-higher-versus-dollar-euro-after-ecb-cuts-rate.html
The pound stayed higher versus the
dollar and the euro after the  European Central Bank  cut its
benchmark interest rate to a record-low 0.5 percent.  Sterling gained 0.2 percent to $1.5582 at 12:49 p.m. London
time and strengthened 0.1 percent to 84.66 pence per euro.  ECB policy makers meeting in Bratislava today lowered the
main refinancing rate to 0.5 percent from 0.75 percent, a move
predicted by 45 of 70 economists in a Bloomberg News survey.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark McCord at 
 mmccord2@bloomberg.net  